## title

### Source (en)

~~~text
Are there qualified references to other data sets?
~~~

### Translation (zh_Hant)

~~~text
是否有指向其他資料集合適的參照？
~~~

## text

### Source (en)

~~~text
A qualified reference is a cross-reference that explains its intent. For example, X is regulator of Y is a much more qualified reference than X is associated with Y, or X see also Y. The goal therefore is to create as many meaningful links as possible between (meta)data resources to enrich the contextual knowledge about the data.
~~~

### Translation (zh_Hant)

~~~text
一個合格的參照（qualified reference）指的是一個能夠說明清楚其意義的交叉參照。舉例來說，「X 是 Y 的調節器（regulator）」比「X 跟 Y 有關聯」或是「X 另見 Y」 更加適合作為參照。因此，參照的目標在於在（後設/詮釋）資料與資料之間，製造有意義的連結，越多越好，以此豐富我們對資料的脈絡了解。
~~~
